main event: An observer reported sighting a reddish-orange object making a humming or whining sound in North Culter, Maine on 16 Dec 67.
interesting points: The object was luminous orange in color., The sighting occurred during cloudy weather., The initial report indicated insufficient data for evaluation., The sighting was not investigated according to regulations., The report was sent back to a local Air Force Base for further investigation but no additional information was submitted.
